core:processNote.core:description:
This process is used to upgrade the client id for a queue consumer definition. If the definition has a client id, no upgrade is performed. Otherwise, a client id is automatically calculated and populated into the service definition. The definition is then saved back to the database before returning.
If a client id is generated, it will also copy the pointer for the old client id (using the Service.DeviceID) to the new id.
This all happens in a single transaction and therefore should be rolledback together in the event of an exception

core:param.value: Failed to populate client id for service definition
core:param.name: enactor.coreUI.LogMessage
